#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. The Third Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Accayasutta → accaya (akodhano) (pts1) | accayasuttaṃ (pts2)
msgctxt "sn11.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Accayasutta "
msgstr "24. Transgression "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn11.24:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ … pe … ārāme. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/are-there-really-two-meanings-for-sampayojeti/4560
msgctxt "sn11.24:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū sampayojesuṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time two mendicants were overly attached, "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.3"
msgid "Tatreko bhikkhu accasarā. "
msgstr "and one of them transgressed against the other. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tassa bhikkhuno santike accayaṃ accayato deseti; "
msgstr "The transgressor confessed to the other mendicant, "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.5"
msgid "so bhikkhu nappaṭiggaṇhāti. "
msgstr "but they didn’t accept it. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.7"
msgid "“idha, bhante, dve bhikkhū sampayojesuṃ, tatreko bhikkhu accasarā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn11.24:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhante, bhikkhu tassa bhikkhuno santike accayaṃ accayato deseti, so bhikkhu nappaṭiggaṇhātī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.514, sc2
msgctxt "sn11.24:2.1"
msgid "“Dveme, bhikkhave, bālā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are two fools. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:2.2"
msgid "Yo ca accayaṃ accayato na passati, yo ca accayaṃ desentassa yathādhammaṃ nappaṭiggaṇhāti—"
msgstr "One who doesn’t recognize when they’ve made a mistake. And one who doesn’t properly accept the confession of someone who’s made a mistake. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:2.3"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, dve bālā. "
msgstr "These are the two fools. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.24:2.4"
msgid "Dveme, bhikkhave, paṇḍitā. "
msgstr "There are two who are astute. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:2.5"
msgid "Yo ca accayaṃ accayato passati, yo ca accayaṃ desentassa yathādhammaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti—"
msgstr "One who recognizes when they’ve made a mistake. And one who properly accepts the confession of someone who’s made a mistake. "

msgctxt "sn11.24:2.6"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paṇḍitā. "
msgstr "These are the two who are astute. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.24:3.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the Thirty-Three, recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.240, sc4
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.1"
msgid "‘Kodho vo vasamāyātu, "
msgstr "‘Control your anger; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.2"
msgid "Mā ca mittehi vo jarā; "
msgstr "don’t let friendships decay. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.3"
msgid "Agarahiyaṃ mā garahittha, "
msgstr "Don’t blame the blameless, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.4"
msgid "Mā ca bhāsittha pesuṇaṃ; "
msgstr "and don’t say divisive things. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.5"
msgid "Atha pāpajanaṃ kodho, "
msgstr "For anger crushes bad people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.24:4.6"
msgid "Pabbatovābhimaddatī’”ti. "
msgstr "like a mountain.’”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
